00:56:30.000 --> 00:56:33.980
You find a lot more
success in discovering

00:56:33.980 --> 00:56:36.130
who do I want to be?

00:56:36.130 --> 00:56:38.580
What's important to me?

00:56:38.580 --> 00:56:42.030
What are the qualities that
I want to develop in myself,

00:56:42.030 --> 00:56:45.390
and then I want to train
myself in those qualities,

00:56:45.390 --> 00:56:47.730
and I want to know why.

00:56:47.730 --> 00:56:51.000
Why do I want to be this
way and not that way?

00:56:51.000 --> 00:56:51.540
Right?

00:56:51.540 --> 00:56:57.350
So like in what way do I
want-- how would I like

00:56:57.350 --> 00:56:59.930
to react in a moment like that?

00:56:59.930 --> 00:57:04.850
And I'm 100% not
going to prescribe

00:57:04.850 --> 00:57:07.490
some sort of a
right way to react,

00:57:07.490 --> 00:57:15.140
but I can say that it is the
inevitable human response when

00:57:15.140 --> 00:57:18.690
you're in touch with
suffering that it brings up

00:57:18.690 --> 00:57:20.700
suffering in you.

00:57:20.700 --> 00:57:25.500
In Buddhist
psychology, the saying

00:57:25.500 --> 00:57:30.470
is that the nature of mind
is dual and permeable.

00:57:30.470 --> 00:57:32.867
If you're really
happy, being around

00:57:32.867 --> 00:57:35.450
you is going to make me happy,
and if you're really suffering,

00:57:35.450 --> 00:57:37.550
being around you is going
to bring up suffering in me.

00:57:37.550 --> 00:57:39.830
The question is, what do I
do with the suffering that

00:57:39.830 --> 00:57:43.240
comes up in me?

00:57:43.240 --> 00:57:46.200
Am I dominated by it?

00:57:46.200 --> 00:57:50.910
Suffering, I would
say, is a good servant

00:57:50.910 --> 00:57:55.530
and a terrible master,
because suffering

00:57:55.530 --> 00:58:00.510
is a necessary
component of compassion.

00:58:00.510 --> 00:58:04.920
There would be no compassion,
if we couldn't suffer.

00:58:04.920 --> 00:58:07.340
So I recognize the
suffering in me,

00:58:07.340 --> 00:58:12.590
and then I want to relate
to that suffering with love

00:58:12.590 --> 00:58:13.250
in myself.

00:58:13.250 --> 00:58:15.734
I want to be able to
accept that in me,

00:58:15.734 --> 00:58:17.150
and I want to be
able to recognize

00:58:17.150 --> 00:58:21.020
that the entire spectrum
of human experience

00:58:21.020 --> 00:58:24.720
is welcome in me.

00:58:24.720 --> 00:58:27.180
I want to make
friends with my anger.

00:58:27.180 --> 00:58:31.997
I don't want to somehow decide
that I shouldn't be angry.

00:58:31.997 --> 00:58:34.580
And that the more that I'm able
to make friends with my anger,

00:58:34.580 --> 00:58:39.500
the more that I'm able to listen
to it and act with wisdom.

